1
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:14,260
♫ When romance is too insignificant ♫

2
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:21,730
♫ But I can't stop missing you, like a bad cold ♫

3
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:28,340
♫ Drifting in a deserted island, where feelings have no reception ♫

4
00:00:28,340 --> 00:00:32,150
♫ Have you been well? ♫

5
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:36,240
♫ Don't worry, I'll be fine ♫

6
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:39,520
♫ Don't worry, I can't fall asleep ♫

7
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:46,860
♫ Don't worry, I can't get used to this lonely world ♫

8
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:53,710
♫ Hitting the pause button, leaving your side ♫

9
00:00:53,710 --> 00:01:00,800
♫ Letting the memories migrate to that day of happiness ♫

10
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:07,130
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:12,990
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:16,190
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,190 --> 00:01:22,100
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:28,650
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,650 --> 00:01:31,190
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,190 --> 00:01:34,310
The Zheng Xiao'en in the book is me.

17
00:01:34,310 --> 00:01:38,490
I thought I just had a very long dream,

18
00:01:38,490 --> 00:01:41,050
but this book shows me

19
00:01:41,050 --> 00:01:43,710
that there was a person who was so good to me.

20
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:45,910
The way my heart beat wasn't fake.

21
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:47,710
The day you were attacked because of your police report...

22
00:01:47,710 --> 00:01:50,710
Did I do something wrong that day?

23
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:54,670
You keep looking at me with a can't-bear-to-let-you-go expression

24
00:01:54,670 --> 00:01:57,960
as though I’ve let you down.

25
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,680
Because the surveillance footage was lost,

26
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:02,940
everyone who was on the rooftop that day is required to come assist with the investigation.

27
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:04,490
Then what do you plan to tell the police?

28
00:02:04,490 --> 00:02:07,950
I plan to cooperate with the investigation and respond honestly.

29
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:12,560
Go buy all of the books that Zheng Xiao'en has handled.

30
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,510
I would like to understand Zheng Xiao'en better.

31
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:17,080
Zheng Xiao'en is the person I'm interested in right now.

32
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:19,140
I must have seen Qingfeng somewhere before.

33
00:02:19,140 --> 00:02:21,250
I want to confirm which books he's wandering in.

34
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:24,530
Even if I'm not happy, Qingfeng has to be happy.

35
00:02:24,530 --> 00:02:28,560
I'm worried. My Supreme Master...

36
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,740
Is he okay?

37
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:40,370
[Lost Romance]

38
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:43,390
[Chapter Seventeen]

39
00:02:56,700 --> 00:03:01,550
[Qingfeng]

40
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:07,190
[Qingfeng]

41
00:03:07,190 --> 00:03:10,050
Zheng Xiao'en! Lin Chuntian!

42
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:11,780
Look at what you guys have done.

43
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:15,030
Our publishing company has received yet another legal attest letter.

44
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,140
- Why?
- Why?

45
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,740
There is a scene in CEO, Don't Stop where the female lead hides in the closet

46
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:22,290
and the male lead comes in to change his clothes.

47
00:03:22,290 --> 00:03:25,510
Rushi Publishing is suing us for plagiarism.

48
00:03:25,510 --> 00:03:28,130
Is there a male lead in a romance novel who doesn't take off his clothes?

49
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:31,570
Is there a female lead in a romance novel who doesn't lust for the male lead's body?

50
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:33,990
I'm not the target audience. I don't care!

51
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:38,690
Anyway, you have to fix this immediately, right now, right away!

52
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:50,540
What do we do?

53
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:55,920
Let's contact the author and see what she says.

54
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:58,630
It's not easy being an author nowadays.

55
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:01,210
The female lead goes to the male lead's house and doesn't want to get caught.

56
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:04,210
If she's not hiding in the closet or bathroom, she's hiding under the bed.

57
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:06,900
- Otherwise, would she be hiding in the refrigerator?
- Exactly.

58
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:09,790
Then it'd become a suspense novel.

59
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:12,860
These are the places that everyone writes about.

60
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,880
They all claim plagiarism at the drop of a hat.

61
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:19,500
If he has the ability, he should find a romance novel whose male lead isn't a CEO, a gang leader, or an emperor.

62
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,490
Exactly! Exactly!

63
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:24,170
It's all just a formula.

64
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,690
Plagiarizing!

65
00:04:37,690 --> 00:04:40,720
That's right, plagiarizing!

66
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:44,110
It's such a good idea. Why didn't I think of this earlier?

67
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:48,110
You want to use plagiarism to create a new series?

68
00:04:48,110 --> 00:04:53,440
No. Remember how we couldn't find the author who wrote the book about Qingfeng's heroic adventure?

69
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,990
Since we can't find him,

70
00:04:55,990 --> 00:04:59,750
then we'll have him come find us.

71
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:14,880
[Love Across the Atlantic]

72
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:21,140
[New Books]

73
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:23,930
[Love Across the Atlantic]

74
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:34,400
Love Across the Atlantic. A longing that stretches across an ocean.

75
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,730
A 10-year search. A 3652-day adventure.

76
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:39,980
Let's turn back the clocks to the beginning of the Republic of China.

77
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:42,920
How does a refined and cultured heir to a noble family of traditional Chinese medicine

78
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:48,920
carve out a niche for the Chinese on the other side of the ocean?

79
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:52,980
If Chief Editor Yao finds out that we wrote up a random description

80
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:55,280
and put it up for sale pretending that it's a book to be published,

81
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,350
we're done for.

82
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,370
If Chief Editor Yao asks you about it, just tell him you don't know anything.

83
00:06:03,370 --> 00:06:05,410
I'll take responsibility for this.

84
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:07,010
If responsibility needs to be taken, we'll take it together.

85
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:11,600
Two people will get a thinner layer of spit when Chief Editor Yao yells.

86
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,090
- Loyalty.
- Loyalty.

87
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,350
I wonder if people read these summaries.

88
00:06:21,350 --> 00:06:24,780
There are, but there aren't many.

89
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:29,560
Will the original author be able to see this?

90
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,630
I don't know.

91
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:02,180
- Why are you here?
- What are you thinking?

92
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:05,290
You only just finished your rehabilitation and you are here swimming.

93
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:07,740
I just want to get better sooner.

94
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:10,800
If you want to get better quickly, you have to follow the rehabilitation plan.

95
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,390
Don't do additional training without permission.

96
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:15,490
You might not get good results and could even get hurt.

97
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:18,430
I know my own body better than anyone else does.

98
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:21,570
Hurry and get up.

99
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:29,370
Hurry, hurry! We're going to be late.

100
00:07:40,090 --> 00:07:41,810
Safe.

101
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:45,050
You guys are plagiarizing.

102
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:49,030
Plagiarizing again?

103
00:07:49,030 --> 00:07:51,390
They're always exaggerating.

104
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:53,550
Who is Cheng Qing?

105
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:57,240
An author I've never even heard of is at our publishing company claiming that we've plagiarized.

106
00:07:57,240 --> 00:08:00,650
You're a scammer, aren't you?

107
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:02,570
Cheng Qing?

108
00:08:03,930 --> 00:08:05,710
You guys are plagiarizing.

109
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:08,940
The book Love Across the Atlantic that you're publishing even has the same name.

110
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,370
And you still say you're not plagiarizing?

111
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:12,780
What Atlantic?

112
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:14,810
We have never released anything like that!

113
00:08:14,810 --> 00:08:16,140
Don't make stuff up!

114
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:18,370
You— Don't even!

115
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:20,860
- It is on your website—
- Who is plagiarizing?

116
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,320
Zheng Xiao'en, you came at the perfect time.

117
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,940
Please explain to this crazy person.

118
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:28,910
Our company has never published any Atlantic, Pacific, or Indian Ocean books!

119
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:34,790
Your name is Cheng Qing? Which characters?

120
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:40,250
Cheng in the characters for procedure.

121
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:42,180
Qing in the characters for grass.

122
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:46,040
What are the names of the male and female leads in the book?

123
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,030
Tell me!

124
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:58,890
The male lead is named Chen Qing, with the common surname Chen.

125
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:05,240
The female lead is named Liu Mushuang.

126
00:09:13,810 --> 00:09:16,010
This is proof.

127
00:09:40,410 --> 00:09:42,660
[For Liu Mushuang]

128
00:09:42,660 --> 00:09:44,910
[For Liu Mushuang]

129
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:47,240
[For Liu Mushuang]

130
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,310
Can I read them?

131
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:57,450
As you wish.

132
00:10:08,590 --> 00:10:12,310
Xiaoshuang, I arrived in Malacca today.

133
00:10:12,310 --> 00:10:16,410
Before I disembarked the ship, the sea breeze blowing towards me was boiling hot because of the sunshine.

134
00:10:16,410 --> 00:10:19,120
It's hard to believe, right?

135
00:10:20,630 --> 00:10:23,460
Since our ship had practically no military equipment,

136
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:26,760
all of the ship’s crew immediately became very worried.

137
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:30,670
Even I, who was deep in my dreams, woke up suddenly due to the commotion.

138
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:43,490
In the past, I was an engineer of a merchant ship sailing the distant seas.

139
00:10:43,490 --> 00:10:49,010
Xiaoshuang is my childhood sweetheart and my first love.

140
00:10:49,010 --> 00:10:51,600
We grew up together.

141
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:56,660
Because I spent a lot of time on the ship,

142
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:59,350
I started writing letters to her

143
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:01,490
because I wanted to tell her

144
00:11:01,490 --> 00:11:05,010
all about the places I had been to and the sceneries I had seen.

145
00:11:05,590 --> 00:11:07,790
Then these letters...

146
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,960
I never sent them.

147
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:15,130
After all, when I left,

148
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:19,660
I didn't even have the courage to tell her to wait for me.

149
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:25,210
The novel was based on these love letters.

150
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:30,540
There would be an adventure to overcome obstacles at each place that he went to.

151
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:34,810
After overcoming these obstacles, he would be able to see Liu Mushuang.

152
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:37,230
Just like how I could also...

153
00:11:42,710 --> 00:11:48,810
I could also muster up the courage to send these letters to Xiaoshuang

154
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:51,380
and let her know how I feel.

155
00:11:55,170 --> 00:12:00,740
I know... I am not a courageous person.

156
00:12:01,830 --> 00:12:06,050
Since that is the case, why did you not finish writing the book?

157
00:12:08,610 --> 00:12:13,130
I put all my heart into this book.

158
00:12:13,130 --> 00:12:18,910
I planned to give the book to Xiaoshuang when I finished and confess my love to her.

159
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:24,260
But I never thought that when I was writing the last chapter—

160
00:12:24,260 --> 00:12:28,220
Was it when the male lead boarded the ship for his return journey?

161
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:32,980
Yes. How did you know?

162
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:50,970
Anyway, I received news that Xiaoshuang had gotten engaged to the town mayor's son.

163
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:56,320
So you stopped writing?

164
00:12:57,180 --> 00:13:01,070
Yes. I burnt the manuscript.

165
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:03,400
Burnt it?

166
00:13:17,310 --> 00:13:20,880
In the end, Chen Qing finally found Liu Mushuang.

167
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:24,980
They planned to return to their country together.

168
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:34,370
Right at the moment when they set foot on their cruise,

169
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:39,780
flames colored the entire sky red.

170
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:46,690
Everything that was before their eyes

171
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:49,490
seemed like it was burning.

172
00:13:56,980 --> 00:13:58,790
You're so irresponsible!

173
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:00,250
So what if you were heartbroken?

174
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:02,480
What did Chen Qing from the book do wrong?

175
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,020
You are already on the last chapter.

176
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:07,330
Can't you finish writing and give him a proper ending?

177
00:14:07,330 --> 00:14:12,180
Why do you have to make Chen Qing in the novel suffer just because you're suffering?

178
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:15,350
I can't write anymore.

179
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:19,830
This book is my love letter.

180
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:21,740
There is no longer a recipient for the love letter.

181
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:24,490
What's the point in continuing to write it?

182
00:14:24,490 --> 00:14:28,410
Mister, it's already the last chapter!

183
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:32,750
Anyway, I didn't come to sue you.

184
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:35,140
It's just that the stories are too similar.

185
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:38,880
I don't know where you got this story,

186
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:43,660
but they are my heartbroken memories after all.

187
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:51,080
If possible, I'd like for you guys to take this book off the shelves.

188
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,600
Mister, listen to me.

189
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:56,770
Finish the story, publish the novel,

190
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:58,660
make a bunch of money, and buy that ship.

191
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:00,820
Show that Xiaoshuang!

192
00:15:00,820 --> 00:15:02,960
I don't want to show off to Xiaoshuang.

193
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:05,530
I want her to be happy.

194
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,030
That is the right attitude.

195
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:11,430
Since you haven't finished writing it,

196
00:15:11,430 --> 00:15:14,920
there is still an opportunity to write a happy ending.

197
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:24,260
Look at how precious these letters are,

198
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:27,450
how real these feelings were.

199
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,800
Even if you don't confess with these,

200
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:33,190
they are still your genuine feelings.

201
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:41,260
How was Harry Potter written?

202
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:45,190
It was the light at the end of the tunnel for a single mother at her darkest hour.

203
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:49,560
And all these adventures are your treasures.

204
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:54,090
If you give up so easily,

205
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,230
don't you think it is a pity?

206
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:08,010
It is the first time someone tells me this.

207
00:16:12,710 --> 00:16:15,820
Do you think there are many authors who personally sailed the five oceans?

208
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:18,880
Do you think there are many authors who are this full of emotion?

209
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:22,480
Do you think there are many authors with such a wild imagination?

210
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:26,040
So you can do it! Really!

211
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:28,010
You have to write it.

212
00:16:28,010 --> 00:16:30,480
I'm begging you to write it well

213
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:33,050
so that Chen Qing can be happy.

214
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:51,080
Our publishing company will definitely publish this book for you.

215
00:16:56,860 --> 00:16:58,750
What do you mean publish it?

216
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,750
I already rejected the proposal to appeal to the male market last time.

217
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,480
We can't even handle the female market.

218
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,520
Why would we appeal to the male market?

219
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:07,990
Chief Editor, there was someone called Huang Yi in Hong Kong.

220
00:17:07,990 --> 00:17:11,050
Everyone told him that the market for wuxia (martial arts) novels was already declining.

221
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:13,630
But, against expectations, he started his own publishing company

222
00:17:13,630 --> 00:17:15,980
to publish his own wuxia novels.

223
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:18,300
So you are going to start your own publishing company?

224
00:17:18,300 --> 00:17:20,580
What Xiao’en meant was we can be the talent scout.

225
00:17:20,580 --> 00:17:22,190
When everyone is doubting us—

226
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,960
It means that stuff is bad.

227
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:27,090
We have to follow the trend and move towards a good place.

228
00:17:27,090 --> 00:17:29,860
A good publishing company has to expand their genres in a timely manner.

229
00:17:29,860 --> 00:17:33,580
That's why I've never boasted that we're a good publishing company.

230
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:35,830
We are a small publishing company.

231
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:38,850
Okay, don't say anymore. No one will take on a business deal that loses money.

232
00:17:38,850 --> 00:17:41,990
No means no.

233
00:17:49,620 --> 00:17:52,940
You guys think I’ve never been young before?

234
00:17:53,870 --> 00:17:55,910
Hey!

235
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,120
I used to be very passionate.

236
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:02,840
I also had ambitions and ideals for the publishing industry.

237
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:05,600
But my dreams were eaten by reality in the end.

238
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,980
A tough man like me

239
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:11,580
still ended up as the chief editor of romance novels.

240
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:15,400
We've already lost money on the last book.

241
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:20,360
Can you guarantee that this book will make a profit?

242
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,930
You can't just do whatever you want at the company.

243
00:18:23,930 --> 00:18:28,510
I'm responsible for everyone's salaries, including both of yours.

244
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:35,690
If the company shuts down, how will I face everyone, including you two?

245
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:48,240
Then, let's think about other ways.

246
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:50,880
After all, the publishing company is not ours alone.

247
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:55,620
You know, I used to bottle everything inside.

248
00:18:55,620 --> 00:18:58,700
Every time my boss made an unreasonable request,

249
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,800
even though I thought it was really stupid,

250
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:05,300
I just thought... why couldn't we communicate?

251
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:09,120
Maybe he would listen to my suggestions.

252
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:12,180
If he's a boss with a brain.

253
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:17,190
Chief Editor, let me discuss with you.

254
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:19,380
I understand your worries.

255
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:24,420
But what if I can think of a way to break even first?

256
00:19:25,690 --> 00:19:28,010
Before this book is published,

257
00:19:28,010 --> 00:19:30,670
whether it’s pulling in sponsorships, selling advertisements, or selling merchandise,

258
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:34,450
I’ll try everything to earn the cost back first.

259
00:19:34,450 --> 00:19:36,320
It won't affect your regular work?

260
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:38,930
Yes, I will work overtime.

261
00:19:38,930 --> 00:19:45,370
If I do this, can we publish this book using this company's name?

262
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:49,810
You really want to publish this book this badly?

263
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:55,160
Yes. This book is very important to me.

264
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,780
I can also work overtime.

265
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:04,550
I know that talking about its great significance

266
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:07,060
makes me sound like an eighth grader (early teen with delusions of grandeur).

267
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:09,530
But it was not easy to find this author.

268
00:20:09,530 --> 00:20:12,350
I really can't give up.

269
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:18,290
Please, Chief Editor.

270
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:20,500
Please.

271
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:26,790
Fine. I won't ask that this book earn a profit.

272
00:20:26,790 --> 00:20:30,490
As long as it doesn't lose money, we will publish it.

273
00:20:30,490 --> 00:20:32,610
- Thank you, Chief Editor!
- You are the human Bodhisattva.

274
00:20:32,610 --> 00:20:35,020
- The Buddha reborn.
- You're our great benefactor.

275
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:38,160
Enough. Hurry and get back to work.

276
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,450
Go. Go.

277
00:20:40,450 --> 00:20:42,430
Thank you, Chief Editor.

278
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:45,910
Enough. Go.

279
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:57,640
[Ruge Publishing]

280
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:08,350
How was it?

281
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:11,290
This is the list of vendors who rejected the business department.

282
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:15,220
They said we are more than welcome to try it ourselves.

283
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:16,460
I will go there now.

284
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:19,730
Wait. Drink something first.

285
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:28,160
Do you have a plan for the ad inserts in the book?

286
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:32,500
The client said they would consider it, but we don't have enough physical channels.

287
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,410
I'm going to get in touch with various convenience stores.

288
00:21:35,410 --> 00:21:39,160
But the procurement process for convenience stores is really difficult.

289
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:44,550
But if we close the deal, our publishing company will have secured a basic sales market.

290
00:21:48,690 --> 00:21:50,460
I think you have changed.

291
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:51,890
How?

292
00:21:51,890 --> 00:21:54,520
You are more positive and courageous than before.

293
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:58,430
In the past, you wouldn't have lasted more than five seconds with Chief Editor Yao.

294
00:21:58,430 --> 00:22:02,960
Could it be that CEO, You're So Naughty is actually some spiritual growth class?

295
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:10,330
Some things you just shouldn't think too much about.

296
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:13,270
Just hurry up and do what you feel like doing.

297
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:20,020
I like you, so I have to let you know.

298
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:21,940
Say it again.

299
00:22:21,940 --> 00:22:25,880
I like you.

300
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,290
Again.

301
00:22:27,290 --> 00:22:29,060
I like you.

302
00:22:36,650 --> 00:22:40,070
Senior Xiao'en, look into my eyes.

303
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:44,750
The Xiao'en of yesterday is as if she died yesterday.

304
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:49,360
The Xiao'en of today is as if she was born today.

305
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:53,310
What are you saying?

306
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:55,150
I'm saying we should get back to work.

307
00:22:55,150 --> 00:22:57,460
We don't care for a CEO who isn't ours.

308
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,290
A conscientious woman is most beautiful.

309
00:22:59,290 --> 00:23:02,340
There has to be a CEO who will be for me.

310
00:23:03,130 --> 00:23:07,050
That's right. I don't need to think fondly back to the CEO every day.

311
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:10,140
Compared to the past when I didn't know what I could do,

312
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:12,530
at least I have a direction to go in now.

313
00:23:12,530 --> 00:23:17,140
Next, I just need to run towards my goal.

314
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:20,380
I feel so much better now.

315
00:23:20,380 --> 00:23:22,460
Goodbye, CEO.

316
00:23:23,130 --> 00:23:26,180
Goodbye, CEO.

317
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,890
The police contacted us.

318
00:23:41,890 --> 00:23:43,340
When the CEO recovers a bit more,

319
00:23:43,340 --> 00:23:46,030
we need to go to the police station to assist with their investigation.

320
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:49,300
- Regarding Zheng Xiao'en's police report?
- Yes.

321
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:53,390
Also, He Tianjian and He Mingli have already been to the police station.

322
00:23:53,390 --> 00:23:55,790
They already went? How did it go?

323
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:58,330
I am not sure yet.

324
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:03,940
Have He Mingli's people gotten in touch with you?

325
00:24:07,260 --> 00:24:09,160
Zheng Xiao'en.

326
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:13,490
Don't say I am not helping you.

327
00:24:14,580 --> 00:24:16,550
Helping me with what?

328
00:24:16,550 --> 00:24:19,920
You know how I went to headquarters today for a meeting?

329
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:23,570
During the meeting, I got wind of some gossip.

330
00:24:23,570 --> 00:24:25,100
Gossip?

331
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:28,590
I heard that all the big publishing companies are fighting over it.

332
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:33,720
They all want to release a book in collaboration with the person who's the hottest topic right now.

333
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,230
Who?

334
00:24:35,230 --> 00:24:37,590
If we can get him first—

335
00:24:37,590 --> 00:24:38,790
Who is it?

336
00:24:38,790 --> 00:24:41,420
Do you really need to ask? He Tianxing, of course!

337
00:24:41,420 --> 00:24:43,690
- Who?
- Who?

338
00:24:43,690 --> 00:24:46,270
Have you been living under a rock?

339
00:24:46,270 --> 00:24:50,010
Ever since Tianliang Group's CEO He Tianxing woke up after falling off a building,

340
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:52,440
his popularity exploded.

341
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:57,790
Be it his bizarre history or handsome appearance, they are all hot topics.

342
00:24:57,790 --> 00:25:03,220
Do you know which piece of news had the highest click-through rate last week?

343
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:05,730
He Tianxing's cane

344
00:25:05,730 --> 00:25:09,010
hit a tree on the street.

345
00:25:13,310 --> 00:25:14,750
The day after that news broke,

346
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:18,120
everyone got out their cameras to take a picture of that tree.

347
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:20,890
The point is, he's very popular right now.

348
00:25:20,890 --> 00:25:25,290
Anything related to him will definitely break click-through rate records.

349
00:25:25,290 --> 00:25:27,250
So?

350
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:29,860
So as long as we get He Tianxing,

351
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:34,270
regardless of whether we publish an autobiography, a photo book, a finance book,

352
00:25:34,270 --> 00:25:37,020
or even just a piece of paper, it's all good.

353
00:25:37,020 --> 00:25:42,130
If we can get He Tianxing, it is just like getting a money tree.

354
00:25:43,090 --> 00:25:45,600
Tree.

355
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:59,470
Chief Editor, I also want you to help you earn this money,

356
00:25:59,470 --> 00:26:04,250
but there's this very small misunderstanding between He Tianxing and me.

357
00:26:04,250 --> 00:26:07,790
I'm afraid it wouldn't be appropriate to see him again.

358
00:26:07,790 --> 00:26:11,530
I'm afraid it'd be like an ant trying to shake a tree or a praying mantis trying to stop a car with its arm.

359
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:14,130
Zheng Xiao'en.

360
00:26:14,130 --> 00:26:17,170
- Was it you who wanted to publish the novel?
- Yes.

361
00:26:17,170 --> 00:26:21,790
Aren't you the one with a passionate eighth grader's dream?

362
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:23,230
Yes.

363
00:26:23,230 --> 00:26:25,680
I am supporting you so much right now.

364
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,090
Where's your eighth grader's dream?

365
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:29,410
Did it get extinguished just like that?

366
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:32,260
No. It has not been extinguished yet.

367
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:35,330
Good. Then why have you not already on your way?

368
00:26:35,330 --> 00:26:37,030
Good luck!

369
00:27:00,810 --> 00:27:03,150
[Email from Zheng Xiao'en]

370
00:27:03,150 --> 00:27:04,540
Hello, Mr. He.

371
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:07,510
I am Zheng Xiao'en, an editor from Ruge Publishing.

372
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:08,960
I am sorry to bother you.

373
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:11,660
I was wondering if you had time for an interview?

374
00:27:11,660 --> 00:27:15,020
Or do you have plans to publish an autobiography?

375
00:27:15,020 --> 00:27:17,420
[Read]

376
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:29,860
Didn't he read it already?

377
00:27:29,860 --> 00:27:32,580
Why isn't he replying?

378
00:27:52,850 --> 00:27:55,760
We've been completely ignored.

379
00:27:57,530 --> 00:28:01,310
Looks like there is only one option left.

380
00:28:01,310 --> 00:28:03,650
What option?

381
00:28:03,650 --> 00:28:06,560
[Jenn Lann Temple]

382
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:09,450
Ta-da! Ask the gods for help.

383
00:28:09,450 --> 00:28:13,290
Have you forgotten that we always come here whenever we can't come up with a solution?

384
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:16,890
When you were in the hospital, I didn't forget to light a lantern for you.

385
00:28:16,890 --> 00:28:19,790
See? Aren't you all better now?

386
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:25,450
So this time, earnestly asking Mazu for help is the right thing to do.

387
00:28:27,850 --> 00:28:31,620
This afternoon, Tianliang Group CEO He Tianxing suddenly fell from a building.

388
00:28:31,620 --> 00:28:34,100
After life-saving measures, he has been temporarily put in the intensive care unit for continued monitoring.

389
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:35,710
At any rate, he's been saved.

390
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:39,820
There's hope as long as he's still alive.

391
00:28:39,820 --> 00:28:44,940
I will definitely pray for you and light lanterns at the temple for your speedy recovery.

392
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:52,390
[Jenn Lann Temple]

393
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:03,330
I'll go buy the offerings. You go and get the incense.

394
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:30,060
Where's the incense?

395
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:57,410
Let's go.

396
00:30:19,940 --> 00:30:22,390
I thought I was forcing you to come here.

397
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:25,460
I didn't expect that you would pray more sincerely than I did.

398
00:30:25,460 --> 00:30:27,800
What did you ask for? You were praying for so long.

399
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:29,900
- He Tianxing.
- That’s the way to go!

400
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,550
That his leg would recover quickly.

401
00:30:31,550 --> 00:30:34,450
What? No way.

402
00:30:34,450 --> 00:30:36,700
Shouldn't you be praying that He Tianxing would agree to let us interview him,

403
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,190
that Chief Editor Yao would allow us to publish the book without any problems,

404
00:30:38,190 --> 00:30:40,860
that you and I make a fortune and save for our pension,

405
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:42,790
that we won’t be cheated by bad guys and scammers,

406
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:47,450
and that we'll happily live our retirement lives together without worrying about food or clothing?

407
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:51,310
Zheng Xiao’en, I’ve finally seen through you.

408
00:30:51,310 --> 00:30:56,320
Hey! Actually, there's something I haven't told you.

409
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:58,290
What?

410
00:30:59,490 --> 00:31:02,610
The day after I saw the news about He Tianxing's accident,

411
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:07,240
I actually came to pray for Mazu's blessing and protection.

412
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:10,270
So what if you came? Why didn't you tell me?

413
00:31:11,390 --> 00:31:13,690
I looked down on myself.

414
00:31:15,850 --> 00:31:19,730
I knew very well that the first thing I should've done is report it to the police.

415
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,590
It wasn't even a stranger.

416
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:24,340
We had been watching him for so long.

417
00:31:24,340 --> 00:31:29,000
In my heart, he was like a familiar neighbor.

418
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:31,950
A one-sided familiarity.

419
00:31:31,950 --> 00:31:36,130
That's right, a one-sided familiarity.

420
00:31:36,130 --> 00:31:40,510
But I didn't even dare to write an anonymous letter.

421
00:31:40,510 --> 00:31:43,940
So I came to see Mazu

422
00:31:43,940 --> 00:31:48,230
to ask her what I needed to do to save He Tianxing.

423
00:31:48,230 --> 00:31:49,930
On the premise that you don’t reveal your identity

424
00:31:49,930 --> 00:31:52,960
or let others know that you’ve been spying on him?

425
00:31:55,930 --> 00:31:58,430
I feel that Mazu's very powerful.

426
00:31:58,430 --> 00:32:01,440
She sent you on a fantastic journey for three months,

427
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:06,370
under the premise of revealing neither your identity nor the fact that you were spying.

428
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:11,470
She's powerful. I'm going to buy a protective talisman.

429
00:32:11,470 --> 00:32:14,550
You go first. I want to take a look in the back.

430
00:32:14,550 --> 00:32:16,570
Let's meet up at the main entrance later.

431
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:18,630
Okay.

432
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:34,010
Excuse me.

433
00:32:37,490 --> 00:32:40,870
"May you live a long and happy life together." This is great!

434
00:32:40,870 --> 00:32:43,540
That's not right. I don't even have a boyfriend.

435
00:32:43,540 --> 00:32:45,540
Who would I live a long and happy life together with?

436
00:32:45,540 --> 00:32:47,810
[May you be promoted to a higher position]
This one is good!

437
00:32:47,810 --> 00:32:52,050
But if I'm promoted to a higher position, I'd be in Chief Editor Yao's position.

438
00:32:52,050 --> 00:32:54,730
That's unrealistic.

439
00:32:54,730 --> 00:32:57,620
“A healthy body” is still the most realistic!

440
00:33:05,740 --> 00:33:08,550
Jason, are you done buying it?

441
00:33:10,620 --> 00:33:13,030
It's you.

442
00:33:13,030 --> 00:33:15,440
Do I know you?

443
00:33:16,620 --> 00:33:22,010
Look, I bet you this colleague has a secret crush on him.

444
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:26,020
No, you don't.

445
00:33:27,410 --> 00:33:30,950
Why do I feel a strange sense of familiarity?

446
00:33:33,270 --> 00:33:36,360
Hello, I am Ruge Publishing's editor, Lin Chuntian.

447
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:38,950
It really must be fate that I meeting you here.

448
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:41,640
Ruge Publishing?

449
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,320
Is Zheng Xiao'en here too?

450
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:46,880
Of course. Xiao’en is inside right now praying for Mr. He

451
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:49,430
to have good health and a successful business.

452
00:33:49,430 --> 00:33:53,180
Go. Find Tianxing and tell him we need to leave.

453
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:56,330
Hold on. Can I take up a little bit of your time?

454
00:33:56,330 --> 00:34:00,490
I don't know if you received our invitation for an interview?

455
00:34:01,790 --> 00:34:03,680
It wasn't enough that you were spying on him?

456
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:07,610
I can't believe you guys are stalking Tianxing just to interview him.

457
00:34:07,610 --> 00:34:10,010
What stalking?

458
00:34:10,490 --> 00:34:11,950
Hey! Who's stalking you?

459
00:34:11,950 --> 00:34:14,390
Even if we are asking you for a favor, you can’t just falsely accuse us!

460
00:34:14,390 --> 00:34:16,820
Then why are you here?

461
00:34:16,820 --> 00:34:20,780
Does Mazu belong to you? Why can't I be here?

462
00:34:45,590 --> 00:34:48,500
[He Tianxing]

463
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:50,480
I found it.

464
00:34:51,970 --> 00:34:55,130
This is the lantern you lit?

465
00:34:55,130 --> 00:34:56,930
Yeah.

466
00:34:56,930 --> 00:35:00,980
Then why is my name on it?

