00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:23,610
Why don’t you tell me about your family situation?

755
00:56:23,610 --> 00:56:26,200
My family situation?

756
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:32,200
It’s very simple. My family has one member. Me.

757
00:56:33,770 --> 00:56:35,430
What do you mean?

758
00:56:35,430 --> 00:56:39,550
I don't have a dad, a mom, nor any siblings.

759
00:56:43,190 --> 00:56:44,990
I'm not lying.

760
00:56:44,990 --> 00:56:46,690
I was abandoned at a park.

761
00:56:46,690 --> 00:56:49,430
I grew up at an orphanage.

762
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:53,490
Which orphanage?

763
00:56:53,490 --> 00:56:56,510
Yongxin Orphanage.

764
00:56:56,510 --> 00:57:00,470
But it doesn’t exist anymore. It closed down.

765
00:57:02,170 --> 00:57:04,070
I really couldn't tell.

766
00:57:04,070 --> 00:57:07,690
Of course. This is not a matter worth broadcasting.

767
00:57:07,690 --> 00:57:11,240
If it were you, would you like it if everyone looked at you with sympathy

768
00:57:11,240 --> 00:57:15,040
or the feeling of not knowing what to do to make things better?

769
00:57:19,790 --> 00:57:22,030
Indeed, I wouldn’t like it.

770
00:57:23,590 --> 00:57:25,860
Wait a moment. Who should be the one asking the next question?

771
00:57:25,890 --> 00:57:28,280
- I’m confused.
- I think it’s me.

772
00:57:28,280 --> 00:57:30,970
That can’t be. You asked me about my family situation just now.

773
00:57:30,970 --> 00:57:34,560
But you also asked me whether I would like it if everyone looked at me with sympathetic expressions.

774
00:57:34,560 --> 00:57:36,590
That counts as a question?

775
00:57:36,590 --> 00:57:38,620
Yes.

776
00:58:00,020 --> 00:58:02,230
Thank you for accepting the interview today.

777
00:58:02,230 --> 00:58:05,000
Next time, I’ll work harder.

778
00:58:11,730 --> 00:58:13,970
Zheng Xiao'en.

779
00:58:29,250 --> 00:58:32,940
♫ See you around, will you miss me? ♫

780
00:58:32,940 --> 00:58:36,520
♫ Don't miss home too much when it's time to party ♫

781
00:58:36,540 --> 00:58:38,850
♫ And I'm leaving home ♫

782
00:58:38,850 --> 00:58:43,390
♫ Don't think it's where I belong ♫

783
00:58:43,390 --> 00:58:46,810
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

784
00:58:46,810 --> 00:58:52,890
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

785
00:58:52,890 --> 00:58:59,370
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

786
00:58:59,780 --> 00:59:01,950
Thank you for accepting the interview today.

787
00:59:01,950 --> 00:59:04,580
Next time, I’ll work harder.

788
00:59:11,500 --> 00:59:13,480
Zheng Xiao'en.

789
00:59:28,670 --> 00:59:32,920
I have a feeling that you and I...

790
00:59:32,920 --> 00:59:34,990
CEO.

791
00:59:39,680 --> 00:59:41,920
Chuchu?

792
00:59:43,670 --> 00:59:46,420
I finally get to see you.

793
00:59:48,780 --> 00:59:51,160
She is?

794
00:59:54,220 --> 00:59:56,300
I’ll go first. See you tomorrow.

795
00:59:56,300 --> 00:59:58,250
See you tomorrow.

796
00:59:59,970 --> 01:00:01,740
I've been really worried about you,

797
01:00:01,740 --> 01:00:03,890
but back when you were at the hospital,

798
01:00:03,890 --> 01:00:07,030
Sister Shanna would never let me go in to see you.

799
01:00:14,230 --> 01:00:18,550
Does our promise back then still count?

800
01:00:21,110 --> 01:00:23,490
Didn't I tell you that it's my late mother's birthday today?

801
01:00:23,490 --> 01:00:25,270
The chairman organized a very important meeting.

802
01:00:25,270 --> 01:00:30,260
If you don't show up, the directors who are close to He Mingli and He Tianjian definitely won't let you off easy.

803
01:00:30,260 --> 01:00:32,130
Leave.

804
01:00:34,370 --> 01:00:36,590
Tianxing.

805
01:00:37,570 --> 01:00:40,520
Just leave. Let me have some peace and quiet.

806
01:01:01,090 --> 01:01:02,470
CEO.

807
01:01:02,470 --> 01:01:06,700
You're... from the Secretary's Office?

808
01:01:08,370 --> 01:01:10,270
Why are you crying?

809
01:01:11,410 --> 01:01:15,250
My father passed away yesterday.

810
01:01:15,250 --> 01:01:18,080
Why didn't you take time off if your father passed away?

811
01:01:18,080 --> 01:01:19,970
I didn't dare to.

812
01:01:22,460 --> 01:01:30,370
Shanna. Help... Ling Chuchu arrange for time off for a week.

813
01:01:31,900 --> 01:01:37,860
In the past, my dad often said that he would take me to see a sunrise,

814
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:43,210
but we were never able to go because of work.

815
01:01:43,740 --> 01:01:47,990
Every time, he would say, "We'll go next time for sure."

816
01:01:48,780 --> 01:01:54,190
Who knew there would never be a next time?

817
01:01:57,470 --> 01:01:59,700
That's how life is.

818
01:02:00,740 --> 01:02:05,290
For some people, when you want to celebrate their birthday,

819
01:02:06,180 --> 01:02:08,540
the opportunity disappears forever instead.

820
01:02:08,540 --> 01:02:12,520
Let's see a sunrise together next time.

821
01:02:15,050 --> 01:02:16,980
I'm sorry.

822
01:02:16,980 --> 01:02:22,520
I just feel like you also really need to see a sunrise.

823
01:02:25,720 --> 01:02:27,900
Let's go if we have the chance.

824
01:02:33,250 --> 01:02:35,470
Since you suddenly got into an accident,

825
01:02:35,470 --> 01:02:40,970
I just want to know if our promise still counts.

826
01:02:43,850 --> 01:02:46,590
I know, I'm not talking about now.

827
01:02:46,590 --> 01:02:48,720
Things are different now.

828
01:02:48,720 --> 01:02:51,910
A lot of things have happened.

829
01:02:51,910 --> 01:02:56,310
I just want to confirm whether you're still

830
01:02:56,310 --> 01:02:59,980
the same person who encouraged and protected me.

831
01:03:01,000 --> 01:03:03,260
Not Tianliang's CEO,

832
01:03:03,260 --> 01:03:06,860
but just He Tianxing.

833
01:03:08,120 --> 01:03:11,630
♫ Lost to you ♫

834
01:03:11,630 --> 01:03:20,800
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

835
01:03:20,800 --> 01:03:23,740
♫ If you were a painter ♫

836
01:03:23,740 --> 01:03:27,030
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

837
01:03:27,030 --> 01:03:33,160
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

838
01:03:33,160 --> 01:03:39,600
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

839
01:03:44,420 --> 01:03:46,270
I think Cheng Qing mailed that to us.

840
01:03:46,270 --> 01:03:48,900
I think so too, but I don't know if he likes it or not.

841
01:03:48,900 --> 01:03:49,990
It's hard to say.

842
01:03:49,990 --> 01:03:52,670
Good. This is a really good beginning.

843
01:03:52,670 --> 01:03:55,230
Cheng Qing really is a hidden gem.

844
01:03:55,230 --> 01:03:59,020
Have him continue to write the rest of the story. Make it fast.

845
01:04:00,290 --> 01:04:01,360
What are you laughing at?

846
01:04:01,360 --> 01:04:03,810
As a dutiful chief editor of romances,

847
01:04:03,810 --> 01:04:06,340
I shouldn't be reading these types of novels to begin with.

848
01:04:06,340 --> 01:04:07,590
Yes, yes, yes.

849
01:04:07,590 --> 01:04:08,860
You're totally right, Chief Editor.

850
01:04:08,860 --> 01:04:11,950
Hurry up and discuss how we're going to publish He Tianxing's autobiography.

851
01:04:11,950 --> 01:04:14,800
What method will we be using, and where will it be released?

852
01:04:14,800 --> 01:04:16,310
We thought of a few approaches.

853
01:04:16,310 --> 01:04:17,800
"The CEO's fifty secrets."

854
01:04:17,800 --> 01:04:19,300
"I have a date with the CEO."

855
01:04:19,300 --> 01:04:20,970
"Those years, the CEO we chased after together."
(Reference to the Taiwanese film You Are the Apple of My Eye)

856
01:04:20,970 --> 01:04:23,910
"There has to be a CEO out there who suits you."

857
01:04:33,080 --> 01:04:35,860
We weren't planning on finding a PR company at first,

858
01:04:35,860 --> 01:04:38,090
but because we're publishing a book for He Tianxing,

859
01:04:38,090 --> 01:04:41,970
a lot of PR companies have been contacting us to collaborate in mutual benefit.

860
01:04:41,970 --> 01:04:44,000
Zheng Xiao'en, stop laughing.

861
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:45,030
Sorry, I can't stop.

862
01:04:45,030 --> 01:04:46,930
What's wrong with Zheng Xiao'en?

863
01:04:46,930 --> 01:04:48,890
Is she under too much pressure from work?

864
01:04:48,890 --> 01:04:51,050
I didn't exploit her too much, did I?

865
01:04:51,050 --> 01:04:53,440
Does she need to take some time off?

866
01:04:55,530 --> 01:04:58,210
It's nothing. Sorry.

867
01:04:58,210 --> 01:05:01,520
Chief Editor, can someone else handle the interviews with He Tianxing?

868
01:05:01,520 --> 01:05:03,080
This...

869
01:05:03,080 --> 01:05:04,340
Let me switch with you.

870
01:05:04,340 --> 01:05:07,250
Let me handle contacting the inside front cover's designer and the printing press.

871
01:05:07,250 --> 01:05:08,680
That works, right? That works, right?

872
01:05:08,680 --> 01:05:10,090
You were the one who secured this interview.

873
01:05:10,090 --> 01:05:12,790
That works, right?

874
01:05:12,790 --> 01:05:14,770
Okay.

875
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:23,240
My goodness. I've laughed so hard my stomach hurts.

876
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:34,810
Zheng Xiao'en, what's going on with you?

877
01:05:34,810 --> 01:05:36,110
Nothing much.

878
01:05:36,110 --> 01:05:40,060
There is something. Anytime He Tianxing is mentioned, you...

879
01:05:46,190 --> 01:05:51,140
I thought I already passed over the CEO and went straight to business.

880
01:05:53,730 --> 01:05:55,720
It turns out I didn't.

881
01:05:56,900 --> 01:05:58,990
It turns out I couldn't.

882
01:05:59,890 --> 01:06:01,670
What's wrong?

883
01:06:04,920 --> 01:06:08,630
I already know that Situ Aoran is Situ Aoran

884
01:06:08,630 --> 01:06:11,560
and that He Tianxing is He Tianxing.

885
01:06:16,410 --> 01:06:19,020
But when I went to conduct the interview,

886
01:06:20,020 --> 01:06:25,190
I couldn't help but try to find

887
01:06:25,190 --> 01:06:28,020
traces of Situ Aoran on He Tianxing.

888
01:06:32,940 --> 01:06:36,430
From the moment I asked him if he was afraid of the dark,

889
01:06:36,430 --> 01:06:39,360
wasn't that a form of not letting go?

890
01:06:42,940 --> 01:06:47,680
He said he wasn't afraid, and I was hurt.

891
01:06:49,470 --> 01:06:51,920
But what if he said he was afraid?

892
01:06:52,770 --> 01:06:57,420
I would think, "That's right! You are Situ Aoran!"

893
01:06:57,420 --> 01:06:59,960
"You just don't know it."

894
01:07:13,960 --> 01:07:16,650
When he was talking about his past,

895
01:07:18,610 --> 01:07:24,110
I couldn't help but make comparisons with Situ Aoran's life experiences.

896
01:07:25,270 --> 01:07:28,390
When he was asking about my personal information,

897
01:07:28,390 --> 01:07:32,410
I wondered if he took an interest in me.

898
01:07:32,410 --> 01:07:36,450
When he was walking me out, I even thought that

899
01:07:36,450 --> 01:07:39,970
maybe we'd still have a chance.

900
01:07:43,360 --> 01:07:45,830
And then Chuchu appeared,

901
01:07:47,820 --> 01:07:51,110
reminding me that real life is real life.

902
01:07:54,270 --> 01:07:57,480
I feel like I'm so pitiful for overthinking things.

903
01:07:59,990 --> 01:08:04,150
Who knew that there would also be a Chuchu in real life?

904
01:08:05,510 --> 01:08:07,940
Aoran dreamt about her before.

905
01:08:09,300 --> 01:08:13,970
She presented He Tianxing with a thousand paper cranes on behalf of the company.

906
01:08:15,600 --> 01:08:18,690
I thought she was just called Chuchu as well.

907
01:08:20,620 --> 01:08:23,230
Who knew that

908
01:08:23,230 --> 01:08:27,930
this Chuchu would be the same Chuchu?

909
01:08:34,430 --> 01:08:39,270
That's why I really can't go anymore. Really.

910
01:08:40,300 --> 01:08:42,380
I can't go anymore.

911
01:08:56,050 --> 01:08:58,250
CEO, if I win,

912
01:08:58,250 --> 01:09:01,520
can I make a wish to have a pair of cufflinks you wear often?

913
01:09:01,520 --> 01:09:03,960
It’s like watching live streamers compete through a screen.

914
01:09:03,960 --> 01:09:05,720
I don't even have the qualifications to donate to them.

915
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:08,400
I'm a complete outsider.

916
01:09:08,400 --> 01:09:09,920
Why didn't you show up as promised?

917
01:09:09,920 --> 01:09:13,220
I trusted you, yet you chose to run away just as we were getting started.

918
01:09:13,220 --> 01:09:16,820
If you’re such an irresponsible person,

919
01:09:16,820 --> 01:09:18,410
I'll be very disappointed.

920
01:09:18,410 --> 01:09:21,400
I used to think that we were people from different worlds,

921
01:09:21,400 --> 01:09:23,390
but the more I come to understand you,

922
01:09:23,390 --> 01:09:28,640
the more I feel that you're not that far out of reach after all.

923
01:09:28,640 --> 01:09:31,650
Didn't I say that as long as I reach out my hand,

924
01:09:31,650 --> 01:09:33,910
I must be able to touch you?

925
01:09:48,560 --> 01:09:51,800
♫ Memories wear protective coloration ♫

926
01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:54,910
♫ Ambushing in the middle of the night ♫

927
01:09:54,910 --> 01:09:58,890
♫ A quiet strike ♫

928
01:10:00,390 --> 01:10:03,590
♫ Streetlights awaiting dusk ♫

929
01:10:03,590 --> 01:10:05,890
♫ Still awaiting as always ♫

930
01:10:05,890 --> 01:10:08,990
♫ Nothing is impossible ♫

931
01:10:08,990 --> 01:10:13,390
♫ Even if no one is perfect ♫

932
01:10:13,390 --> 01:10:17,990
♫ Holding you next to my heartbeat ♫

933
01:10:17,990 --> 01:10:21,190
♫ Tightly held the palm of my hand ♫

934
01:10:21,190 --> 01:10:26,190
♫ It remains the only farewell ♫

935
01:10:26,190 --> 01:10:30,890
♫ If I could see you again ♫

936
01:10:30,890 --> 01:10:37,590
♫ Carefully planning my gamble with you ♫

937
01:10:37,590 --> 01:10:41,690
♫ In the end I lost to you ♫

938
01:10:41,690 --> 01:10:50,890
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

939
01:10:50,890 --> 01:10:54,660
♫ If you were a painter ♫

940
01:10:54,660 --> 01:10:56,760
♫ Then I'll be your canvas ♫

941
01:10:56,760 --> 01:11:01,060
♫ No regrets ♫

942
01:11:01,060 --> 01:11:06,860
♫ I lost all my love to you ♫
